#set up imports, define some functions
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import math

def extract_gene_id(x):
    info_parts = x.split('|')
    return info_parts[0]

def extract_gene_name(x):
    info_parts = x.split('|')
    return info_parts[1]

def log_trans(x):
    try:
        return math.log(x, 10)
    except:
        return float('NaN')

average_gene_tpms_df = gene_tpms_df[['gene', 'gene_id', 'gene_name']]
for genotype in ['WT', 'EDF1_ko']:
    for treatment in ['UN120', 'EM30', 'EM120']:
        av_sample = f'{genotype}_{treatment}'
        average_gene_tpms_df[av_sample] = sum([gene_tpms_df[f'{av_sample}_r{rep}'] for rep in range(1,4)])/3.0
average_gene_tpms_df.to_csv('average_gene_TPMs.tsv', sep='\t', index=False)

#plot fold changes
%matplotlib inline
import matplotlib as mpl
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import scipy.stats as stats
import numpy as np
from adjustText import adjust_text
import math

plt.rcParams['pdf.fonttype'] = 42 #leaves most text as actual text in PDFs, not outlines
##plot CDF or mRNA RPKMs
black = (0,0,0)
gray = (0.5,0.5,0.5)
orange = (230/255.0,159/255.0,0)
skyBlue = (86/255.0,180/255.0,233/255.0)
bluishGreen = (0,158/255.0,115/255.0)
yellow = (240/255.0,228/255.0,66/255.0)
blue = (0,114/255.0,178/255.0)
vermillion = (213/255.0,94/255.0,0)
reddishPurple = (204/255.0,121/255.0,167/255.0)
colors = [black, orange, skyBlue, bluishGreen, vermillion, blue, reddishPurple, yellow]
rainbow = [black, vermillion, orange, bluishGreen, blue, reddishPurple, 'violet']

datasets = average_gene_tpms_df.columns.tolist()[3:]
num_plots_wide = len(datasets)
num_plots_high = num_plots_wide
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(2*num_plots_wide, 2*num_plots_high))
plot_index = 1

df = average_gene_tpms_df

for i in range(len(datasets)):
    for j in range(len(datasets)):
        plot = fig.add_subplot(num_plots_high, num_plots_wide, plot_index)
        if j < i:
            df.plot.scatter(datasets[j], datasets[i], color=black, s=1, alpha=1, ax=plot)
            plot.set_xlabel(datasets[j])
            plot.set_ylabel(datasets[i])
            plot.set_xscale('log', basex=2)
            plot.set_yscale('log', basey=2)
            plot.set_ylim(10**-3, 10**5)
            plot.set_xlim(10**-3, 10**5)
        elif j == i:
            #no point comparing same dataset
            plot.spines['left'].set_visible(False)
            plot.spines['bottom'].set_visible(False)
            plot.set_xticks([])
            plot.set_yticks([])
        else:
            #plot the correlations up top
            subset_df = pd.DataFrame()
            subset_df[datasets[i]] = df[datasets[i]].apply(log_trans)
            subset_df[datasets[j]] = df[datasets[j]].apply(log_trans)
            subset_df=subset_df.dropna()
            pr, pp = stats.pearsonr(subset_df[datasets[j]], subset_df[datasets[i]])
            sr, sp = stats.spearmanr(subset_df[datasets[j]], subset_df[datasets[i]])
            plot.set_xlabel(datasets[j])
            plot.set_ylabel(datasets[i])
            plot.text(-4.5, -2, 'r=%.3f\nrho=%.3f\n' % (pr, sr), fontsize=16)
            plot.set_ylim(-5, 5)
            plot.set_xlim(-5, 5)
            plot.set_xticks([])
            plot.set_yticks([])
        plot.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
        plot.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
        plot.set_aspect('equal')
        plot_index+=1

#lg=plt.legend(loc=4,prop={'size':12}, labelspacing=0.2)
#lg.draw_frame(False)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('average_gene_TPM_corr.pdf', transparent='True', format='pdf')
plt.savefig('average_gene_TPM_corr.png', transparent='True', format='png')

#first make volcano plots for major 3 comparisons - EDF1 vs WT and emetine treatments
significance_datasets = [EDF1ko_vs_WT_inUN, EM30_vs_UN_inWT, EM120_vs_UN_inWT, EM30_vs_UN_inEDF1ko, EM120_vs_UN_inEDF1ko, EM30_vs_UN_EDF1ko_interaction, EM120_vs_UN_EDF1ko_interaction]
dataset_names = [u'UN, EDF1/WT', 'WT EM30/UN', 'WT EM120/UN', u'EDF1 EM30/UN', u'EDF1 EM120/UN', u'EDF1 effect on EM30', u'EDF1 effect on EM120']
tpm_data = average_gene_tpms_df
padj_cutoff = 0.01

x_var = 'log2FoldChange'
y_var = '-log padj'

num_plots_wide = len(significance_datasets)
num_plots_high = 1
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(3*num_plots_wide, 3*num_plots_high))
plot_index = 1

for comparison_index  in range(len(significance_datasets)):
    plot = fig.add_subplot(num_plots_high, num_plots_wide, plot_index)
    
    #pull out significant hits
    sig_dataset = significance_datasets[comparison_index]
    sig_p = sig_dataset[sig_dataset['padj']<padj_cutoff]
    insig_p = sig_dataset[sig_dataset['padj']>padj_cutoff]
    fos_jun = sig_dataset[sig_dataset['gene_name'].isin(['FOS', 'JUN'])]
    edf1 = sig_dataset[sig_dataset['gene_name'].isin(['EDF1'])]
    #make scatterplots
    insig_p.plot.scatter(x_var, y_var, color=gray, s=1, alpha=1, ax=plot, label='other')
    sig_p.plot.scatter(x_var, y_var, color=black, s=1, alpha=1, ax=plot, label='padj<%.2f' %(padj_cutoff))
    fos_jun.plot.scatter(x_var, y_var, color=vermillion, s=3, alpha=1, ax=plot, label='FOS, JUN')
    edf1.plot.scatter(x_var, y_var, color=bluishGreen, s=3, alpha=1, ax=plot, label='EDF1')
    
    #adjust axes
    plot.set_title(dataset_names[comparison_index])
    plot.set_xlabel(x_var)
    plot.set_ylabel(y_var)
    #plot.set_xscale('log', basex=2)
    #plot.set_yscale('log', basey=2)
    plot.set_ylim(0, 250)
    plot.set_xlim(-10, 10)
    plot.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    plot.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    #plot.set_aspect('equal')
    plot.get_legend().remove()
    plot_index+=1

lg=plot.legend(loc=1,prop={'size':12}, labelspacing=0.2)
lg.draw_frame(False)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('volcano.pdf', transparent='True', format='pdf')
plt.savefig('volcano.png', transparent='True', format='png')

#first make volcano plots for major 3 comparisons - EDF1 vs WT and emetine treatments
significance_datasets = [EDF1ko_vs_WT_inUN]
dataset_names = [u'UN, EDF1/WT']

tpm_data = average_gene_tpms_df
padj_cutoff = 0.01

x_var = 'log2FoldChange'

'''
M is the population size (previously N)
n is the number of successes in the population (previously K)
N is the sample size (previously n)
X is still the number of drawn successes.
We can then compute a probability of drawing X red marbles out of N from a jar containing n red marbles out of M in the following way:
from scipy.stats import hypergeom
pval = hypergeom.sf(x-1, M, n, N)
'''
from scipy.stats import hypergeom

plot_index = 1

for comparison_index  in range(len(significance_datasets)):
    plot = fig.add_subplot(num_plots_high, num_plots_wide, plot_index)
    
    #pull out significant hits
    sig_dataset = significance_datasets[comparison_index]
    sig_p_up = sig_dataset[(sig_dataset['padj']<padj_cutoff) & (sig_dataset['log2FoldChange']>log2FC_cutoff)]
    sig_p_down = sig_dataset[(sig_dataset['padj']<padj_cutoff) & (sig_dataset['log2FoldChange']<-1*log2FC_cutoff)]
    sig_tpms_up = tpm_data[tpm_data['gene_id'].isin(sig_p_up['gene_id'].tolist())]
    sig_tpms_down = tpm_data[tpm_data['gene_id'].isin(sig_p_down['gene_id'].tolist())]
    insig_tpms = tpm_data[~tpm_data['gene_id'].isin(sig_p_up['gene_id'].tolist()+sig_p_down['gene_id'].tolist())]
    fos_jun = tpm_data[tpm_data['gene_name'].isin(['FOS', 'JUN'])]
    edf1 = tpm_data[tpm_data['gene_name'].isin(['EDF1'])]

    dataset_pair = TPM_dataset_pairs[comparison_index]
    insig_tpms.plot.scatter(dataset_pair[0], dataset_pair[1], color=gray, s=1, alpha=1, ax=plot, label='other')
    sig_tpms_up.plot.scatter(dataset_pair[0], dataset_pair[1], color=orange, s=1, alpha=1, ax=plot, label='up, padj<%.2f, log2FC %.2f' %(padj_cutoff, log2FC_cutoff))
    sig_tpms_down.plot.scatter(dataset_pair[0], dataset_pair[1], color=reddishPurple, s=1, alpha=1, ax=plot, label='down, padj<%.2f, log2FC %.2f' %(padj_cutoff, -1*log2FC_cutoff))
    fos_jun.plot.scatter(dataset_pair[0], dataset_pair[1], color=vermillion, s=3, alpha=1, ax=plot, label='FOS, JUN')
    edf1.plot.scatter(dataset_pair[0], dataset_pair[1], color=blue, s=3, alpha=1, ax=plot, label='EDF1')
    #write the correlations up top
    subset_df = pd.DataFrame()
    subset_df[dataset_pair[0]] = tpm_data[dataset_pair[0]].apply(log_trans)
    subset_df[dataset_pair[1]] = tpm_data[dataset_pair[1]].apply(log_trans)

dfs = [EDF1ko_vs_WT_inUN, EM30_vs_UN_inWT, EM120_vs_UN_inWT, EM30_vs_UN_inEDF1ko, EM120_vs_UN_inEDF1ko, EM30_vs_UN_EDF1ko_interaction, EM120_vs_UN_EDF1ko_interaction]

#Now plot emetine changes (both timepoints) in WT against those in emetine at the same timepoint

log2FC_data = combined_deseq_log2fc_df
comparison_pairs = [(u'WT EM30/UN', u'EDF1 EM30/UN'), (u'WT EM120/UN', u'EDF1 EM120/UN')]
num_plots_wide = len(comparison_pairs)
num_plots_high = 1
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(3*num_plots_wide, 3*num_plots_high))
plot_index = 1

for dataset_pair in comparison_pairs:
    plot = fig.add_subplot(num_plots_high, num_plots_wide, plot_index)
    
    #pull out FOS and JUN and sig effects of EDF1ko on emetine treatment
    fos_jun = log2FC_data[log2FC_data['gene_name'].isin(['FOS', 'JUN'])]    
    edf1 = log2FC_data[log2FC_data['gene_name'].isin(['EDF1'])]    

    #make scatterplots
    log2FC_data.plot.scatter(dataset_pair[0], dataset_pair[1], color=gray, s=1, alpha=1, ax=plot, label='other')
    fos_jun.plot.scatter(dataset_pair[0], dataset_pair[1], color=vermillion, s=3, alpha=1, ax=plot, label='FOS, JUN')
    edf1.plot.scatter(dataset_pair[0], dataset_pair[1], color=blue, s=3, alpha=1, ax=plot, label='EDF1')
    plot.plot(range(-4,5), range(-4,5), linestyle='dashed', color=blue)
    #write the correlations up top
    subset_df = pd.DataFrame()
    subset_df[dataset_pair[0]] = log2FC_data[dataset_pair[0]]
    subset_df[dataset_pair[1]] = log2FC_data[dataset_pair[1]]
    subset_df=subset_df.dropna()
    pr, pp = stats.pearsonr(subset_df[dataset_pair[0]], subset_df[dataset_pair[1]])
    sr, sp = stats.spearmanr(subset_df[dataset_pair[0]], subset_df[dataset_pair[1]])
    #plot.text(10**-2.5, 10**3.5, 'r=%.3f, rho=%.3f\n' % (pr, sr), fontsize=10)
    #label most significant hits
    top_hits = log2FC_data[log2FC_data['gene_name'].isin(EM120_vs_UN_inWT.sort_values(by=['padj'])[:10]['gene_name'])]
    texts = []
    for x, y, s in zip(top_hits[dataset_pair[0]], top_hits[dataset_pair[1]], top_hits['gene_name']):
        texts.append(plot.text(x, y, s))
        #adjust_text(texts, only_move={'points':'y', 'text':'y'})
    #adjust axes
    plot.set_xlabel('%s log2FC' % dataset_pair[0])
    plot.set_ylabel('%s log2FC' % dataset_pair[1])
    #plot.set_xscale('log', basex=2)
    #plot.set_yscale('log', basey=2)
    plot.set_ylim(-3, 4)
    plot.set_xlim(-3, 4)
    plot.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    plot.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    plot.set_aspect('equal')
    plot.get_legend().remove()

    plot_index+=1
plt.tight_layout()

lg=plot.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(2.5,0.1), loc="lower right")
lg.draw_frame(False)
plt.savefig('emetine_changes_in_WT_v_ko.pdf', transparent='True', format='pdf')
plt.savefig('emetine_changes_in_WT_v_ko.png', transparent='True', format='png')
